                  </persName>
            . I was at the prisoner's house between seven and eight o'clock that Sunday night; I saw two beds in her shop, one in a window, and the other in a chair.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17690628-61-person616">
                  Elizabeth 
                  Redford 
               <interp inst="t17690628-61-person616" type="surname" value="Redford"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17690628-61-person616" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17690628-61-person616" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live at the end of George-street. Last Sunday, at twelve in the day, she sent for me. I saw some goods there. I made an agreement with her for a bed, which I was to fetch on the Monday morning. She was<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="176906280048"></xptr> drying things before the fire. She supped with me between eight and nine, and I went with her in the night and carried a candlestick and candle, and lent her another candle, which she lighted by mine.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17690628-61-person617">
                  John 
                  Rundle 
               <interp inst="t17690628-61-person617" type="surname" value="Rundle"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17690628-61-person617" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17690628-61-person617" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was at the prisoner's house on Saturday morning the 24th of June, about ten o'clock. I saw two or three little children in bed on the floor; I also saw some chairs and other things, to a great number.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17690628-61-person618">
                  John 
                  Mesure 
               <interp inst="t17690628-61-person618" type="surname" value="Mesure"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17690628-61-person618" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17690628-61-person618" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I have known her above eight years. I never heard any body give her a bad character.</p>
